## Building a Form with Validation in React

**Mental model:** Keep `values`, `errors`, and `touched` as three maps. Validation is a pure function `values -> errors`. Show a field's error only once it's been touched (or after a submit attempt). Submit is blocked while any error exists. This separates *what's wrong* from *what to show*.

### Step 1 — Three state maps
```jsx
const [values, setValues] = useState({ name: '', email: '', password: '' });
const [touched, setTouched] = useState({});
```

### Step 2 — Pure validation function
```jsx
const validate = (v) => {
  const e = {};
  if (!v.name.trim()) e.name = 'Required';
  if (!/^[^@]+@[^@]+\.[^@]+$/.test(v.email)) e.email = 'Invalid email';
  if (v.password.length < 8) e.password = 'Min 8 characters';
  return e;
};
const errors = validate(values);
```

### Step 3 — Show errors only when touched
```jsx
const showError = (k) => (touched[k] || submitted) && errors[k];
<input onBlur={() => setTouched((t) => ({ ...t, [k]: true }))} />
```

### Step 4 — Gate submit
```jsx
const onSubmit = (e) => {
  e.preventDefault();
  setSubmitted(true);
  if (Object.keys(errors).length === 0) { /* submit */ }
};
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Untouched fields | Don't show errors until touched/submit. |
| Submit with errors | Mark all touched, reveal all errors, block. |
| Live re-validate | `errors` recomputes each render from `values`. |

**Interview tip:** Deriving `errors` from `values` on every render (a pure validator) plus a `touched` map for display is the clean separation — it's exactly the model Formik/React-Hook-Form formalize.

