## Building a Form with Validation in Vue 3

**Mental model:** Keep `values`, `touched`, and a `submitted` flag. Validation is a `computed` mapping `values -> errors` (a pure function). Show a field's error only when touched or after submit. Block submit while errors exist.

### Step 1 — Reactive values + touched
```js
const values = reactive({ name: '', email: '', password: '' });
const touched = reactive({});
```

### Step 2 — Errors as a computed
```js
const errors = computed(() => {
  const e = {};
  if (!values.name.trim()) e.name = 'Required';
  if (!/^[^@\s]+@[^@\s]+\.[^@\s]+$/.test(values.email)) e.email = 'Invalid email';
  if (values.password.length < 8) e.password = 'Min 8 chars';
  return e;
});
```

### Step 3 — Show when touched/submitted
```vue
<small v-if="(touched[f.key] || submitted) && errors[f.key]">{{ errors[f.key] }}</small>
```

### Step 4 — Gate submit
```js
function onSubmit() { submitted.value = true; if (Object.keys(errors.value).length === 0) done.value = true; }
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Untouched | Hide error until touched/submit. |
| Submit invalid | Reveal all, block. |
| Live re-validate | `computed` recomputes on input. |

**Interview tip:** A `computed` errors map over a `reactive` values object is the idiomatic Vue form core — pure validation + a touched map for display, which is what VeeValidate builds on.

