## Building a Form with Validation in Angular

**Mental model:** Keep `values`, `touched`, and a `submitted` flag as fields. Validation is a getter mapping `values -> errors`. Show a field's error only when touched or after submit; block submit while errors exist. (Here we hand-roll it without `ReactiveFormsModule` to show the mechanics.) Classic `NgModule` setup, no `?.`/`??` (the build rejects them).

### Step 1 — Fields
```typescript
values: Record<string, string> = { name: '', email: '', password: '' };
touched: Record<string, boolean> = {};
submitted = false;
```

### Step 2 — Errors getter
```typescript
get errors(): Record<string, string> {
  const e: Record<string, string> = {};
  if (!this.values['name'].trim()) { e['name'] = 'Required'; }
  if (!/^[^@\s]+@[^@\s]+\.[^@\s]+$/.test(this.values['email'])) { e['email'] = 'Invalid email'; }
  if (this.values['password'].length < 8) { e['password'] = 'Min 8 chars'; }
  return e;
}
```

### Step 3 — Show when touched/submitted
```html
<small *ngIf="(touched[f.key] || submitted) && errors[f.key]">{{ errors[f.key] }}</small>
```

### Step 4 — Gate submit
```typescript
onSubmit(): void { this.submitted = true; if (Object.keys(this.errors).length === 0) { this.done = true; } }
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Untouched | Hide error until touched/submit. |
| Submit invalid | Reveal all, block. |
| Live re-validate | Getter re-runs each change detection. |

**Interview tip:** Mention `ReactiveFormsModule` (`FormGroup` + `Validators`) as the production path — but hand-rolling `values`/`touched`/`errors` shows you understand the model those abstractions provide.

